<div class="section">
  <h2>Step-by-Step Acquisition Guides</h2>
  <h3>Method 1: Direct Assignment/Transfer</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Identify desired frequency & region (see Carrier tables above)</li>
    <li>Request license details from current holder (AT&T, Verizon, T-Mobile, Select Spectrum, Ligado)</li>
    <li>Negotiate risks, price, exclusivity level, geographic area</li>
    <li>Complete FCC-formalized assignment/transfer paperwork (FCC Form 603: <a href="https://www.fcc.gov/licensing-databases/forms" class="deep-link" target="_blank">FCC Licensing Forms</a>)</li>
    <li>FCC approval, transaction completion</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Method 2: Licensing/Leasing/Subleasing</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Contact carrier, broker, or SAS provider (see above)</li>
    <li>Define exact premises, coverage, use case, term</li>
    <li>Negotiate contract (specifying exclusivity, duration, regulatory compliance)</li>
    <li>File lease/sublease paperwork (FCC Form 608 where required)</li>
    <li>Site readiness, radio deployment, start service</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Method 3: CBRS PAL Acquisition (via SAS)</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Determine location and demand (see CBRS opportunities)</li>
    <li>Contact SAS (such as Federated Wireless)</li>
    <li>Request PAL/GAA availability and exclusivity levels</li>
    <li>Negotiate lease, sign agreement, ensure CBSD hardware integration</li>
    <li>Begin exclusive access as per contract and FCC GAA/PAL rules</li>
  </ol>
</div>

